resourceList.title: Customer Success Story: Wikimedia
resourceList.description: When a massive, global DDoS attack rendered Wikimedia's sites inaccessible, they turned to Cloudflare to protect their network infrastructure and bring them back online quickly

resourceList.title: Demystifying the Internet
resourceList.description: The Internet has become the bloodline for the majority of the businesses today, but do we really understand the evolution of the Internet and the implications it has on our businesses?

resourceList.title: State of 2020 DDoS threat landscape
resourceList.description: Learn about the evolving DDoS threat landscape from Cloudflare's vantage point, as the product team shares 2020 DDoS trends and observations.

resourceList.title: Blog: State of 2020 DDoS threat landscape
resourceList.resourceTitle: Blog: State of 2020 DDoS threat landscape
resourceList.description: Learn about the evolving DDoS threat landscape from Cloudflare's vantage point, as the product team shares 2020 DDoS trends and observations.

resourceList.title: Threat Intel on Cloudflare's Network
resourceList.description:
With 13% of the Internet in our purview, Cloudflare has a unique perspective on the Internet -- newly registered domains, phishing attacks, and more. 

During this session, Malavika Balachandran Tadeusz will share new trends we've observed and how we're building more threat intel into our Cloudflare platform.

resourceList.title: CISO Topic: A tale of two executives - the CEO and the CISO
resourceList.resourceTitle: CISO Topic: A tale of two executives - the CEO and the CISO
resourceList.description:
The CEO and CISO need to be a tag team that lock arms to take the business and technical challenges head on. 
Learn how, in this episode with Cloudflare executives - Matthew Prince, CEO at Cloudflare and Joe Sullivan, CSO at Cloudflare.

resourceList.title: CISO Topic: How can CISOs succeed as a business leader
resourceList.resourceTitle: CISO Topic: How can CISOs succeed as a business leader
resourceList.description:
Security leaders of today and the future are expected to be not just technology leaders but also business leaders. To be successful as a business leader a CISO needs to master concepts including business, marketing, finance and more. 

Learn how, with Joe Sullivan as he shares his insights and experiences as a CSO.

resourceList.title: 3 trends shaping the future of workforce security
resourceList.resourceTitle: 3 trends shaping the future of workforce security
resourceList.description:
For many teams, the sudden migration to remote work forced 3 years of security innovation into 3 months, as IT put an increased focus on enabling secure remote access. 

In this session, Sam Rhea, will share the business and technology currents driving the evolution of Cloudflare for Teams.

resourceList.title: The Death of Hardware Boxes and the Rise of the Cloud
resourceList.resourceTitle: The Death of Hardware Boxes and the Rise of the Cloud
topic: Secure Teams, Devices, and Internal Applications
resourceList.description: The 'Bolt On' appliance based approach is a misfit in today's world which is centered around the user. With the rise of the Cloud there is a need for a 'Built-in' approach.

resourceList.title: The Future of Application Security
resourceList.description: Software development has evolved dramatically in the past decade, which also requires new application security techniques to build a strong security posture for the future. What does the future of application security hold?

resourceList.title: CISO Topic: Institutionalizing Incident Response
resourceList.description: The 3 keys for incident response are risk reduction, crisis preparation and communication. Watch @Joe Sullivan, CSO of Cloudflare, share his thoughts on how security leaders can implement incident response in their organizations.

resourceList.title: Building a Scalable, Secure, Reliable & Performant Network Fabric
resourceList.resourceTitle: Building a Scalable, Secure, Reliable & Performant Network Fabric
resourceList.description: A scalable network fabric that delivers cloud services in a secure, fast and reliable manner is a key tenet of the digital transformation that businesses are experiencing today. How is Cloudflare building this scalable network?

resourceList.title: The Future of Networks and Network Security
resourceList.resourceTitle: The Future of Networks and Network Security
resourceList.description: With the advent of the cloud, a major architectural shift is underway at the network layer. What does the future hold for network and network security?

resourceList.title: CISO Topic: Building a Strong & Diverse Security Team
resourceList.resourceTitle: CISO Topic - Building a Strong & Diverse Security Team
resourceList.description: Diversity is of paramount importance when it comes to building strong teams. Learn from two exemplary security leaders __Jim Routh, CISO MassMutual__ and __Joe Sullivan, CSO Cloudflare__, who have made diversity a part of their team's DNA as they share the why and how of building a diverse team.

resourceList.title: State of Application Security
resourceList.description: Learn about the evolving application threat landscape from Cloudflare's vantage point, as the product team shares State of the Application Security.
